The program is meant to augment the city’s contact tracing efforts, which are a long-standing tool of public health to battle infectious disease outbreaks.
Contact tracing involves interviewing people who test positive for the virus about their recent interactions with others and their movements in public.
Once people resume interacting with others, the hope is that contact tracing will help quell future outbreaks of COVID-19.
“From the beginning of this pandemic, we have emphasized contact tracing.
Massachusetts started a widespread coronavirus contact tracing program this month and said it was the first state to do so.